{"id": "EUVD-2022-55631", "enisaUuid": "fcb64450-41d2-3827-a5cd-abe38c6c9d00", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfs: fix UAF/GPF bug in nilfs_mdt_destroy\n\nIn alloc_inode, inode_init_always() could return -ENOMEM if\nsecurity_inode_alloc() fails, which causes inode->i_private\nuninitialized. Then nilfs_is_metadata_file_inode() returns\ntrue and nilfs_free_inode() wrongly calls nilfs_mdt_destroy(),\nwhich frees the uninitialized inode->i_private\nand leads to crashes(e.g., UAF/GPF).\n\nFix this by moving security_inode_alloc just prior to\nthis_cpu_inc(nr_inodes)", "datePublished": "2025-09-17T14:56:23", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-23T13:29:06", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d1ff475d7c83289d0a7faef346ea3bbf90818bad", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c0aa76b0f17f59dd9c9d3463550a2986a1d592e4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ec2aab115eb38ac4992ea2fcc2a02fbe7af5cf48", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/70e4f70d54e0225f91814e8610477d65f33cefe4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1e555c3ed1fce4b278aaebe18a64a934cece57d8", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/64b79e632869ad3ef6c098a4731d559381da1115", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/81de80330fa6907aec32eb54c5619059e6e36452", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2a96b532098284ecf8e4849b8b9e5fc7a28bdee9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2e488f13755ffbb60f307e991b27024716a33b29", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50367"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50367"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "12663799-6937-347d-a09d-a359061c4219", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <d1ff475d7c83289d0a7faef346ea3bbf90818bad"}, {"id": "262cf0a8-26c3-355d-8c5d-6711c24aec9f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2.6.12"}, {"id": "2be908a4-7e2f-319c-baf7-c5dca5dfb6db", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <2e488f13755ffb